{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9b3a249-99e9-4a2e-b479-6e797ab6d000","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"49774853-8ff7-4165-8140-e819e3e7498d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"A041:19BCF6:17FE4D6:1B4B83F:69FE8A58"},"id":"5e5ac86d-c03a-41aa-adda-9f4bb8514e2f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:14:06.723Z","parentId":"9ff30af1-5d97-4517-befd-a91994661356"}
